channel.title: How to load maps
channel.description: hello everyone, i'm not really into client coding so i would like to know something.. i'm using a 194 look-alike client that uses 289 maps i think.. i have the original 194 just i don't know how to replace the 289 with the 194. any help?

item.title: How to load maps
item.dc:creator: @Vain1 Vain_
item.description:
@Vain1 wrote:

if i recall correctly; both the map format and cache format changed drastically from 194-289.

you will need to get the 194 deob, and 289 deob. and check the map formats.
write/find a map dumper for the 194’s ugly cache format, and dump the maps.

then take the data from the 194 maps and make sure it has the appropriate amount of data for the 289 maps, and if not ~~ insert the data needed
